  "title": "Japan’s NTT Docomo to set up $4b Web3-focused firm",
  "slug": "japans-ntt-docomo-set-4b-web3focused-firm",
  "status": "publish",
  "type": "post",
  "link": "https://www.techinasia.com/japans-ntt-docomo-set-4b-web3focused-firm",
  "content": "<p>Japanese mobile operator giant <a href=\"https://www.docomo.ne.jp/english/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">NTT Docomo</a> has set aside between 500 billion yen and 600 billion yen (between US$3.4 billion and US$4 billion) to invest in Web3 tech, <em><a href=\"https://asia.nikkei.com/Business/Technology/NTT-Docomo-to-invest-4bn-in-Web3\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Nikkei Asia</a></em> reported.</p>\n<p>It will use the funds to set up a company that will develop blockchain-centered solutions, a source told <em>Nikkei Asia</em>. It will begin operating in 2023.</p>\n<p>The development is not NTT Docomo’s first Web3 push. Earlier this year, the firm announced that <a href=\"https://coinstats.app/news/RT8P4JIVZf_Japanese-Telecom-Giant-NTT-Docomo-Launches-%24412-Million-Metaverse-Unit/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">it had opened up a unit</a> dedicated to the metaverse. <a href=\"https://www.nttqonoq.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Qonoq</a> was last said to have 200 staff.</p>\n<p>With a <a href=\"https://coinstats.app/news/RT8P4JIVZf_Japanese-Telecom-Giant-NTT-Docomo-Launches-%24412-Million-Metaverse-Unit/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">budget of US$412 million</a>, Qonoq is focused on several functions, including the creation of metaverse experiences through XR World as well as virtual concert channel Matrix Stream. It is also allowing businesses to set up “digital twins” in this virtual reality, and it is developing hardware to make its metaverse experiences more immersive.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>See also: <a href=\"https://www.techinasia.com/top-funded-startups-tech-companies-japan\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Meet the 50 top-funded startups and tech companies in Japan</a> </strong></p>\n<p><em>Currency converted from Japanese yen to US dollars: US$1 = 146.71 yen.</em></p>",
